==English==
{{wikipedia|YA}}
===Etymology 1===
Reduced form of {{m|en|you}}. Compare {{cog|nl|je}}, reduced/unstressed form of {{m|nl|jij||you}}.
====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|en|/jə/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-ya.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ə|s=1}}
====Pronoun====
{{en-pron}}
# {{nonstandard spelling of|en|you}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2011|author=Byron Douglas|title=A Journey Through the Life of an Anti-Social|ISBN=9781456874520|chapter=3|url={{gbooks|N-3jQqLfVVsC|64|altpg=64–65}}|passage=Lola got a shocked look on her face then said, “'''Ya''' need to stop actin' jealous if '''ya''' aint, and '''ya''' can't control what I do. '''Ya''' aint my daddy and '''ya''' aint my man. I'll see '''ya''' tomorrah after work if '''ya''' want. Just give me a call, '''ya''' have my number”.}}
